    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Armor pieces for the foot existing in various forms in Europe from Medieval times to the 16th century, comprised of mail or plates enclosing the ankle and lames covering the foot, plus a plate toecap. Some types had a detachable long point for the toecap.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
